h, she smiled and then returned the salute.  Clinking her two bracers together in front of her chest and then urging her horse over to Ariah.  Quickly dismounting, she walked up to Ariah. &quot;I came as quick as I could,&quot; her face was serious as she looked at the younger queen. &quot;You must tell me of these Nitewings, and what you have need of me to do.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 1:33:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> War? </span><hr size=1>  The Amazon dropped from her last tree, slinging her leather pack over her shoulder as she entered the village. Inside were a few more daggers, and her war mask. Dawn needed nothing else for war.. for a fight period. The Amazon Assassin followed the path that her other athelfi had, and stood, joining the group that acquired.<br>
